			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				4 wizards would destroy 1 target.  Shadowstep/yonder/fade. Move on to the next. <br>  <br> A good pvp caster is /NEVER/.. read, NEVER in melee. Unless they are a mage, in which case they are dead. <img src="/images/faces/happy.gif" border=0 alt="happy.gif" height=18 hspace=0 width=18 vspace=0>  <br>  <br> You shadowstep out, if you find yourself still close.. keep running.  Stop when you can shadow step again. <br>  <br> It takes you 1/2 second to cast shadowstep at higher levels. That means it can not be interrupted at ALL due to server lag, and eye-hand communication time of us humans.  The only time it will be interupted was if you didn't stop properly.  The best way to stop is the quick &quot;Sit&quot; stop...  <br>  <br> run. Hit sit then stand immediately after. Dead halt. Shadow step. <br>  <br> You /never/ &quot;have&quot; to be in melee with anyone with good resists. <br>  <br>  <br> --		

